        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 3:10PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 310 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles southeast of White Sands National Park. This thunderstorm was
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
White Sands National Park, Boles Acres, and Oliver Lee State Park.

This includes the following highways...
Highway 70 in New Mexico between mile markers 193 and 200.
Highway 54 in New Mexico between mile markers 41 and 56.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
